      "description": "Genorah v4 — Cinematic Intelligence. Premium frontend design system for Claude Code. Alpha-1 ships A2A L4 protocol layer (Result<T> typed envelope, agent cards at /.well-known/agent.json, embedded Fastify HTTP daemon, AG-UI 16-event emitter, MCP sampling v2 adapter) and tiered 105-agent fleet (10 directors + 95 workers, validators as skills, stateless workers + stateful directors, tiered worktree/in-process isolation). M2 ships persistent single-canvas 3D (R3F + Theatre.js + GSAP + Lenis) + 17 WebGPU-native archetypes (50 total) + Scroll Coherence 6th hard gate. M3 ships Asset Forge 2.0 (5 new MCPs: Rodin Gen-2, Meshy 5, Flux Kontext, Recraft V3, Kling 2.1; recipe-driven composite pipelines; user-global asset cache; cost ledger with downgrade chain; full provenance MANIFEST; Scene Craft 13th quality category). M4 ships Design Beyond Archetypes (generative archetype synthesis, Living Systems runtime with 6 signal types, bespoke Signature DNA 3D marks with uniqueness ledger, Tension Council arbitration, Neuro-aesthetic 14th quality category). M5 ships Built Beyond Limits (streaming pipeline, sqlite-vec cross-project memory graph, self-improving judge calibration, agent marketplace with Deno sandbox, offline-first mode, live synthetic-user streaming, server-driven UI renderer, WebGPU UI effects). M6 ships hardening (885 tests, visual regression, chaos tests, perf tests, migration command) + v4.0.0 GA. Final quality gate 394pt (254 Design Craft + 140 UX Integrity). 7 MCP integrations. 7 npm packages (@genorah/protocol, canvas-runtime, asset-forge, living-system-runtime, generative-archetype, memory-graph, marketplace, sdui, webgpu-effects).",
